text: The COVID-19 pandemic in Dominica is part of the ongoing global viral pandemic of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), which was confirmed to have reached Dominica on 22 March 2020. On 22 March, the country's first case of COVID-19 was announced, a 54-year-old man who returned from the United Kingdom. ==References== Category:Dominica Dominica
title: COVID-19 pandemic in Dominica
